<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1004,2039]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1004,1030]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
First segment fused dorsally to prostomium. Elongated dorsal cirri on segments 1, 2 and 3. The elongated dorsal cirri on segments 2 and 3 are the longest of all 
<taxonomicName box="[743,1046,1040,1066]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[743,951,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
Elongated ventral cirri on segment 2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
