at segment 10 (
<figureCitation box="[478,584,1292,1319]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-50@21.[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 15. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). A—dorsal view. B—ventral view. C—dorsal view of anterior, live. D—parapodia. E—drawing of compound chaetae. F—compound chaetae. G—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479949/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Figs 15A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[595,645,1292,1319]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">16C</figureCitation>
). Body light pink in life (
<figureCitation box="[922,1023,1292,1319]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-50@21.[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 15. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). A—dorsal view. B—ventral view. C—dorsal view of anterior, live. D—parapodia. E—drawing of compound chaetae. F—compound chaetae. G—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479949/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 15C</figureCitation>
). Body brown/orange with numerous dark pigmentation speckles in preserved (formalin/ethanol) state (
<figureCitation box="[908,1050,1328,1355]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-50@21.[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 15. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). A—dorsal view. B—ventral view. C—dorsal view of anterior, live. D—parapodia. E—drawing of compound chaetae. F—compound chaetae. G—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479949/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 15A, B</figureCitation>
). Prostomium slightly wider than long; nuchal organs not visible (
<figureCitation box="[511,649,1364,1391]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16A, D</figureCitation>
). Anterior dorsal edge of prostomium with paired cylindrical antennae ~ 
<quantity box="[165,268,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[344,450,1400,1427]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
). Paired palps ventral to antennae, similar in shape and length to antennae (
<figureCitation box="[1317,1424,1400,1427]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
). Segment 1 fused to prostomium, following segments clearly demarcated (
<figureCitation box="[986,1091,1436,1463]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
). Pair of elongated dorsal cirri [tentacular cirri] on each of segments 1 (~ 
<quantity box="[637,727,1472,1499]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long), 2 (~ 
<quantity box="[857,962,1472,1499]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.42">0.42 mm</quantity>
long) and 3 (~ 
<quantity box="[1135,1240,1472,1499]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.44">0.44 mm</quantity>
long) (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16A, D</figureCitation>
