<quantity box="[581,669,1544,1571]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[742,848,1544,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
). Bulbous, rounded dorsal cirri ~ 
<quantity box="[1222,1309,1544,1571]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long begin on segment 3 continuing posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[572,675,1580,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16C</figureCitation>
). Cylindrical, tapering ventral cirri ~ 
<quantity box="[1088,1174,1580,1607]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long begin on segment 3 continuing posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[444,551,1616,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
). Parapodia uniramous, notopodial chaetae absent; neuropodium with central fascicle containing ~5–9 compound chaetae; one simple emergent acicula (
<figureCitation box="[997,1200,1652,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-50@21.[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 15. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). A—dorsal view. B—ventral view. C—dorsal view of anterior, live. D—parapodia. E—drawing of compound chaetae. F—compound chaetae. G—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479949/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Figs 15D, E, F, G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1212,1291,1652,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">16E, F</figureCitation>
). Compound chaetal shaft cylindrical; thin, flattened pointed blade extended from curved joint (
<figureCitation box="[1074,1175,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-50@21.[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 15. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). A—dorsal view. B—ventral view. C—dorsal view of anterior, live. D—parapodia. E—drawing of compound chaetae. F—compound chaetae. G—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479949/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 15E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1004,2039]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,1724,1750]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Variation.</emphasis>
Only 
<specimenCount box="[388,554,1724,1751]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
were collected. The 
<typeStatus box="[785,881,1725,1751]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">paratype</typeStatus>
matches the 
<typeStatus box="[1027,1128,1724,1750]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">holotype</typeStatus>
, but is also complete with a pygidium, which has a pair of small lobed cirri ~ 
<quantity box="[697,784,1760,1787]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
long, rounded distally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1004,2039]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1796,1822]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[324,681,1796,1822]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[324,681,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Galapagomystides bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[690,751,1797,1823]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically like 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[1032,1155,1796,1822]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aristata">
<emphasis box="[1032,1155,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. aristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[1212,1335,1796,1822]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1212,1335,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1344,1406,1797,1823]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having segment 1 dorsally fused to the prostomium. However, in the phylogenetic analyses 
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[1192,1367,1832,1858]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1192,1367,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1375,1436,1833,1859]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was found to be the sister group to a clade comprising 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[767,889,1868,1894]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aristata">
<emphasis box="[767,889,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. aristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[903,1025,1868,1894]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp. and g.">
<emphasis box="[903,1025,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1033,1175,1868,1895]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="genus">
n. sp. and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Blake and Hilbig" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[1148,1175,1868,1894]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="verenae" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[1148,1175,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis box="[1183,1271,1869,1894]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">verenae</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1278,1376,1868,1895]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[181,1408,279,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-61@7.[177,1411,273,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Maximum Likelihood (ML) tree generated from the concatenation of mitochondrial (COI 16rRNA) and nuclear genes (18S rRNA, 28S rRNA). Numbers on nodes represent ML bootstrap values (above node) and Bayesian posterior probabilities (below node). Values below 50% for ML and 0.70 for posterior probabilities are not shown. ‘*’ indicates G. aristata as the type species of Galapagomystides." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479921/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[185,545,1904,1930]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[185,545,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Galapagomystides bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[556,620,1905,1931]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is restricted to Lau Back-arc Basin between 
<quantity box="[1154,1313,1904,1931]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.305" metricValueMax="2.7199999999999998" metricValueMin="1.89" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="m" value="2305.0" valueMax="2720.0" valueMin="1890.0">1890–2720 m</quantity>
depth. An obvious morphological feature distinguishing 
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[666,840,1940,1966]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[666,840,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[846,906,1941,1967]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the very long cirriform elongated dorsal cirri originating from the first three segments, the longest projecting from segments two and three. The chaetal blades of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,325,2012,2038]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[151,325,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[332,392,2013,2039]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are also notable for being the longest of all 
<taxonomicName box="[885,1189,2012,2038]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undefined-A">
<emphasis box="[885,1093,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="472" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[127,141,2098,2117]" lastBlockId="21.[151,1437,151,213]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="472" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
A 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,151,177]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[341,696,151,177]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[341,696,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Galapagomystides bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[703,763,151,177]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is named after the lead author’s father, Bob Pearson, for his invaluable love and support, and who inspired the lead author’s passion and curiosity for the ocean.
</paragraph>
